 "cells": [
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Project 9 — Local Study Notes Generator\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Turn Raw Text into Notes, Flashcards, and Quizzes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Goal:** Take lesson text and generate study notes, flashcards, quizzes,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"and topic outlines — all locally.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Stack:** Ollama · LangChain · Jupyter\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### What You'll Learn\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Multi-output generation\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Structured flashcard format\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Quiz question generation at different levels\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. Topic outline extraction\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# !pip install -q langchain langchain-ollama pydantic\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Step 1 — Configure LLM\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import requests\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from langchain_ollama import ChatOllama\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from langchain_core.prompts import ChatPromptTemplate\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from langchain_core.output_parsers import StrOutputParser\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from pydantic import BaseModel, Field\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    r = requests.get(\\\"http://localhost:11434/api/tags\\\", timeout=5)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"Ollama running — {len(r.json().get('models', []))} models\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"except: print(\\\"Start Ollama first!\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"llm = ChatOllama(model=\\\"qwen3:8b\\\", temperature=0.2)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"study_material = \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Operating Systems — Process Management\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"A process is a program in execution. Each process has a Process Control Block (PCB)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"containing: process state, program counter, CPU registers, memory management info,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"and I/O status.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Process States: New → Ready → Running → Waiting → Terminated.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"The scheduler moves processes between Ready and Running queues.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Context switching saves the state of the current process and loads the state of\\n\",\n",
    "    \"the next. It involves saving/loading PCBs and is pure overhead — no useful work\\n\",\n",
    "    \"is done during a context switch. Typical cost: 1-10 microseconds.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Scheduling Algorithms:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- FCFS (First Come First Served): Simple but causes convoy effect\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- SJF (Shortest Job First): Optimal average wait time but requires knowing burst time\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Round Robin: Fair, uses time quantum. Too small = overhead, too large = FCFS\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Priority Scheduling: Risk of starvation, solved with aging\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Study material loaded: {len(study_material)} chars\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Step 2 — Generate Cornell Notes\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"cornell_prompt = ChatPromptTemplate.from_messages([\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (\\\"system\\\", \\\"\\\"\\\"Generate Cornell Notes format from the study material:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"CUES (left column) | NOTES (right column)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Key questions/terms | Detailed notes, examples, diagrams\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                   |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"─────────────────────────────────────────\\n\",\n",
    "    \"SUMMARY: 3-5 sentence summary of the entire topic\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Rules:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Cues should be questions that the notes answer\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Notes should be concise bullet points\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Include examples where applicable\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Summary should capture the main concepts\\\"\\\"\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (\\\"human\\\", \\\"Generate Cornell Notes for:\\\\n\\\\n{material}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"cornell_chain = cornell_prompt | llm | StrOutputParser()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"cornell_notes = cornell_chain.invoke({\\\"material\\\": study_material})\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(cornell_notes)\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Step 3 — Generate Flashcards\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"class Flashcard(BaseModel):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    front: str = Field(description=\\\"Question or term\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    back: str = Field(description=\\\"Answer or definition\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    difficulty: str = Field(description=\\\"easy, medium, hard\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"class FlashcardDeck(BaseModel):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    topic: str\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    cards: list[Flashcard]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"flashcard_llm = llm.with_structured_output(FlashcardDeck)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"deck = flashcard_llm.invoke(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    f\\\"Generate 10 flashcards from this material:\\\\n\\\\n{study_material}\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Topic: {deck.topic}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Generated {len(deck.cards)} flashcards\\\\n\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for i, card in enumerate(deck.cards):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"Card {i+1} [{card.difficulty}]:\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"  Q: {card.front}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"  A: {card.back}\\\\n\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Step 4 — Generate Practice Quiz\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"class QuizQuestion(BaseModel):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    question: str\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    options: list[str] = Field(description=\\\"4 options (A-D)\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    correct_answer: str = Field(description=\\\"Letter of correct option\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    explanation: str\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"class Quiz(BaseModel):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    questions: list[QuizQuestion]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"quiz_llm = llm.with_structured_output(Quiz)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"quiz = quiz_llm.invoke(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    f\\\"Generate 5 multiple choice questions:\\\\n\\\\n{study_material}\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"=== PRACTICE QUIZ ===\\\\n\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for i, q in enumerate(quiz.questions):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"Q{i+1}: {q.question}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    for opt in q.options:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        print(f\\\"   {opt}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"   Answer: {q.correct_answer}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"   Explanation: {q.explanation}\\\\n\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Step 5 — Study Session Simulator\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"def study_session(material, num_rounds=2):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"Run an automated study → quiz → review cycle.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(\\\"=== STUDY SESSION START ===\\\\n\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    # Round 1: Key concepts\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    concepts_prompt = ChatPromptTemplate.from_messages([\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        (\\\"system\\\", \\\"List the 5 most important concepts from this material, \\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"         \\\"each with a one-sentence explanation.\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        (\\\"human\\\", \\\"{material}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    ])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    concepts = (concepts_prompt | llm | StrOutputParser()).invoke({\\\"material\\\": material})\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(\\\"KEY CONCEPTS TO LEARN:\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(concepts)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    # Round 2: Self-test\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    quiz = quiz_llm.invoke(f\\\"Generate 3 quiz questions:\\\\n\\\\n{material}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(\\\"\\\\n=== SELF-TEST ===\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    score = 0\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    for i, q in enumerate(quiz.questions):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        print(f\\\"\\\\nQ{i+1}: {q.question}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        for opt in q.options:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            print(f\\\"  {opt}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        print(f\\\"  Correct: {q.correct_answer} — {q.explanation}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"\\\\n=== SESSION COMPLETE ===\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"study_session(study_material)\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## What You Learned\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Cornell Notes** generation from raw text\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Flashcard decks** with structured output\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Quiz generation** with explanations\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Study session automation** combining multiple techniques\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Exercises\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Use your own lecture notes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Add spaced-repetition metadata\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Generate a practice exam from multiple topics\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"---\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"*Next: **10 — Local Code Explainer***\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  }\n",
    " ],\n",
